Comment: I did my normal opening.
He probably did his normal opening.
I decided to attack his pawn.
He obviously protected it.
I took my bishop out hoping to put it in a good posistion.
He moved his pawn one forward probably guessing that I would bring my knight further up the board.
I castled to be on the safe side.
He planned to get his bishop out by moving his pawn forward.
I brung my other knight out.
He protected his knight with his bishop maybe thinking that I would move my bishop to b5.
I attacked his knight.
He attacked my bishop.
I didn't do much about that.
He took my pawn.
I took his pawn with my knight.
He took my bishop.
I took his knight.
He took my knight.
I didn't really have much choice and now I was controling the centre.
He attacked my knight because it was in a strong position.
